  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Agroecological Production and Local Markets in Lower Piura Valley</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In recent years, farmers in the Lower Piura Valley have combined monocropping with conventional technology. The results have been lower yields and soil degradation, as well as poor water use, weak organizations and a growing dependence on the market for commercial products. Without changing practices, their resources and family lives are becoming impoverished. However, CIMAD is promoting agroecology as a development alternative.
The project seeks to enhance living conditions for farmers in the Lower Piura Valley, improving soil and water management with an agroecological approach. With this project, 400 families will reinforce their organizations and receive training, inputs and technical assistance for producing agroecological crops and livestock, guaranteeing their food supply and selling surplus in local and regional markets. Other focuses will be increasing crop and livestock production, linking with local and regional markets and increasing producer organizations&#x2019; abilities to negotiate and influence decision making in defense of food sovereignty. Additionally, the pass-on chain will incorporate 600 new families into the program.</narrative>
  </description>
